CC  Activity of the Bacillus cereus virulence transcriptional activator
CC  PlcR depends on binding to the C-terminal heptapeptide of PapR. PapR is
CC  exported, cleaved extracellularly by the NprB protease, and the active
CC  peptide imported by the oligopeptide permease system OppABCDF.
